Name: Scooty
Description: A scooter (motor scooter) is a motorcycle with an underbone or step-through frame, a seat, and a platform for the rider's feet, emphasizing comfort and fuel economy.

Name: Passion Pro
Description: Passion Pro is among the most popular motorcycles sold by Hero Motocorp, and sports modern, youthful styling. There is also a variant of the Passion Pro, called the Xtec, which packs some convenience-focused tech.

Name: Duke
Description: KTM Duke 200 is powered by an OBD-2 compliant, single-cylinder, 199.5cc, liquid-cooled, fuel-injected engine, which produces 25PS and 19.3Nm. The engine is paired to a 6-speed gearbox. The bike is built on a tubular split-trellis frame, which is suspended on a 43mm not required front USD fork and 10-step-preload-adjustable monoshock at the rear. Braking is handled by a 300mm disc up front and a 230mm rear disc brake. It comes with dual-channel ABS as a standard feature. The bike rolls on 17-inch alloys, which come wrapped in 110-section (front) and 150mm (rear) tubeless MRF tyres. The Duke 200 has a 13.4-litre fuel tank and weighs 159kg (kerb). The seat on this bike is 822mm high, with the ground clearance being 155mm.

Name: Karizma
Description: Hero Honda Karizma was a premium motorcycle manufactured by Hero Honda. It was first launched in May 2003, given a facelifted update with some change in graphics in 2006. After that the Hero Honda was given a cosmetic upgrade and relaunched as Karizma R in 2007. In September 2009, it was supplemented by another variant Karizma ZMR with programmed fuel injection in 2009 .

Name: R15
Description: The Yamaha R15S is powered by a 155 cc air-cooled engine which produces 18.6 PS @ 10000 rpm of power. It has a fuel tank of 11 L and a claimed mileage of 40 kmpl. It is available in one variants.

Name: Apache
Description: The TVS Apache RTR 160 is powered by a 159.7 cc air-cooled engine which produces 16.04 PS @ 8750 rpm of power. It has a fuel tank of 12 L and a claimed mileage of 47 kmpl.
